<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910211-0055</DOCNO><DOCID>910211-0055.</DOCID><HL>   Ernest Michaud Sentenced   To 37 Months in Prison</HL><DATE>02/11/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5E</SO><IN>SECURITIES (SCR)SECURITIES REGULATIONS AND ENFORCEMENTS (RGU)</IN><LP>   BOSTON -- Ernest E. Michaud, who controlled BrandonSecurities Inc. and related firms in Providence, R.I., wassentenced to 37 months in prison, to be followed by threeyears probation for securities fraud, U.S. attorneys heresaid.   Mr. Michaud also was ordered to make restitution of about$1.5 million to defrauded investors. As a condition of hisprobation, Mr. Michaud consented to be barred fromassociation with anyone in the securities industry, U.S.attorneys added.</LP><TEXT>   In December, Mr. Michaud pleaded guilty to one count ofsecurities fraud. He was accused of defrauding 44 investorsin a scheme in which money paid by some investors went toothers as interest.</TEXT></DOC>